; Regression test for issue #1806: Lack of granularity in market pricing
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1806
;
; When a posting has both a lot-value annotation and an explicit @/@@
; transaction cost, --price (-I) should report the realized transaction
; price, not the lot basis.  Previously --price and --basis produced
; identical output because both drew from the lot annotation, making
; the transaction-level gain/loss invisible in the priced account.
;
; The priced view of the options account should make the $93.43 realized
; gain visible by valuing the sell at $1,295.00 (the @ price) and the
; close at $1,200.00 (the @ price) rather than both at the lot basis
; of $1,294.20, which otherwise sums to zero.

2019/01/01 SOLD -1 TSLA 100 16 AUG 19 220 PUT @12.95
    (Expenses:Fees)                            $0.05
    (Expenses:Commission)                      $0.75
    Assets:Brokerage:Options         -1 "TSLA 100 16 AUG 19 220 PUT" {{$1,294.20}} @ $1,295.00
    Assets:Brokerage:Cash                  $1,294.20

2019/01/01 BOT +1 TSLA 100 16 AUG 19 220 PUT @12.00
    (Expenses:Fees)                            $0.02
    (Expenses:Commission)                      $0.75
    Income:Capital:Short                     $-93.43
    Assets:Brokerage:Options         1 "TSLA 100 16 AUG 19 220 PUT" {{$1,294.20}} @ $1,200.00
    Assets:Brokerage:Cash                 $-1,200.77

; --price surfaces the realized transaction prices so the $95.00 gross
; trading gain is visible in the options account.
test reg options --price
19-Jan-01 SOLD -1 TSLA 100 16.. Asse:Brokerage:Options   $-1,295.00   $-1,295.00
19-Jan-01 BOT +1 TSLA 100 16 .. Asse:Brokerage:Options    $1,200.00      $-95.00
end test

; The gross trading gain (sold $1295 / bought $1200 = $95) collapses to
; $-95.00 as the remaining valuation in the options account.
test bal options --price
             $-95.00  Assets:Brokerage:Options
end test

; --basis still reports the lot basis, so the two sides cancel to zero.
test reg options --basis
19-Jan-01 SOLD -1 TSLA 100 16.. Asse:Brokerage:Options   $-1,294.20   $-1,294.20
19-Jan-01 BOT +1 TSLA 100 16 .. Asse:Brokerage:Options    $1,294.20            0
end test

; Without any valuation option, postings stay in the original commodity.
test reg options
19-Jan-01 SOLD -1 TSLA 100 16.. Asse:Brokerage:Options -1 TSLA 100 16 AUG 19 220 PUT -1 TSLA 100 16 AUG 19 220 PUT
19-Jan-01 BOT +1 TSLA 100 16 .. Asse:Brokerage:Options 1 TSLA 100 16 AUG 19 220 PUT            0
end test
